    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1978-09-08T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1978-09-08T15:50:00-05:00" n="39"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d39">
                <head>39. Handwritten Note Prepared by the Ambassador to Israel (<persName
                        corresp="#p_LSW_1">Lewis</persName>)<note n="1" type="source"
                        xml:id="d39fn1">Source: Department of State, <gloss target="#t_US_1"
                            >U.S.</gloss> Embassy Tel Aviv, Principal Officer Program Files, Lot
                        85F104, Personal for Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_LSW_1"
                            >Lewis</persName>—Sensitive Notes 1978. No classification marking. No
                        other record of this meeting has been found.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Camp David</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            from="1978-09-08T16:50:00-04:00" to="1978-09-08T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 8, 1978, 4:50–5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Abbreviated US-Israel Bi-Lateral</hi>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_DM_2">Dayan</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_WE_1"
                        >Weizman</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_BA_2">Barak</persName>, <persName
                        corresp="#p_TA_1">Tamir</persName>, Rubenstein</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_MD_1">MD</gloss>—Want to propose a kind of deal. No freeze on
                    settlem[ents] would be just totally impractical. Believe we have agreed on 3 of
                    4 issues—or can agree—&amp; settlements is left.</p>
                <pb facs="0188" n="153" xml:id="pg_153"/>
                <p>Couldn’t we put on record that we did have our position—&amp; we will come back
                    to it after <hi rend="italic">all other</hi> issues with Egypt are settled. We
                    will come back to it.</p>
                <p>And similarly with regard to <hi rend="italic">Sinai</hi> settlements. Let’s see
                    first if we can agree about everything else. If so, <hi rend="italic">then go
                        back to it. Not</hi> close it.</p>
                <p>For WB, as well as Sinai settlements (though issue is different—(freeze &amp;
                    removal)</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_CV_1">CV</gloss>—Let me think about it. Don’t know how
                    realistic that is to put it off <hi rend="italic">indefinitely.</hi>
                </p>
                <p>(Clarify—not till after Camp David.) Put aside.</p>
                <p>Has some merit. Let me see it.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_MD_1">MD</gloss>—Best from practical pt. of view, freeze of
                    settlers just won’t work.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_CV_1">CV</gloss>—I asked Pres. to raise with <persName
                        corresp="#p_SA_1">Sadat</persName> this afternoon,<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d39fn2">See <ref target="#d28fn23">footnote 23, Document
                        28</ref>.</note> as you asked, that he meet separately on airfields. We’ll
                    now see.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_EW_1">EW</gloss>—He won’t do it. He’ll say talk to <persName
                        corresp="#p_GMAG_1">Gamasy</persName>.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_BA_2">Barak</persName>—No he won’t.</p>
                <p>—Chats with Eli, <persName corresp="#p_RM_1">Rosenne</persName>, &amp; Ezer p.m.
                        <hi rend="italic">Fri. Sept. 7</hi>
                    <note n="3" xml:id="d39fn3">Not further identified, but presumably a misdated
                        reference to discussions held Friday, September 8.</note>
                </p>
                <p>3<note n="4" xml:id="d39fn4">Unclear whether this note references September 8
                        conversations with Rubenstein, <persName corresp="#p_RM_1"
                            >Rosenne</persName>, and <persName corresp="#p_WE_1">Weizman</persName>
                        referenced above (<ref target="#d40fn4">footnote 4</ref>) or <persName
                            corresp="#p_LSW_1">Lewis</persName> is recording a separate thought.
                        Note appears at the top of an overleaf page that is otherwise
                        undated.</note> issues where <gloss target="#t_JC_1">JC</gloss> thinks
                    agreement has been reached which aren’t <hi rend="italic">covered</hi> in our
                        draft:<note n="5" xml:id="d39fn5">Not further identified which specific
                        draft <persName corresp="#p_LSW_1">Lewis</persName> is referring to here.
                        See <ref target="#d28fn8">footnote 8, Document 28</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>West Bank, Gaza sovereignty—to be resolved in final peace treaty w/ Jordan</p>
                <p>Limited armaments in Sinai/East<note n="6" xml:id="d39fn6">
                        <persName corresp="#p_LSW_1">Lewis</persName> wrote “not” above this
                        word.</note> of passes</p>
                <p>Air Strips</p>
            </div>
        </body>
